Step 6. Take the address of the last element of the class using the address operator (e.g., $&\texttt{4})$}\\
\\
\node [draw, text width=6cm, minimum height=20mm, right=of SS] (TS) {\textbf{Threadstatically construct:}\\ \textit{Step 7. Take the address of the first element of the thread using the address operator (e.g., $&\texttt{1})$}\\
Step 8. Take the address of the last element of the thread using the address operator (e.g., $&\texttt{4})$}\\
\\
\node [draw, text width=6cm, minimum height=20mm, right=of TS] (CW) {\textbf{Classwide construct:}\\ \textit{Step 9. Take the address of the first element of the class using the address operator (e.g., $&\texttt{1})$}\\
